## 9. Starter divergence catalog

These come from explicit comments in the leaked `bashSecurity.ts`. Each becomes a detector in v0.

| ID | Construct | Source |
|---|---|---|
| `BACKSLASH_SEMICOLON` | `cmd1 \; cmd2` — splitter normalizes `\;` to `;`, bash sees one command | `validateBackslashEscapedOperators` |
| `BACKSLASH_WHITESPACE` | `echo\ test/...` — splitter decodes to space separator, bash treats as one token | `validateBackslashEscapedWhitespace` |
| `QUOTE_COMMENT_DESYNC` | `'x'#` — close-quote and `#` desync quote tracking | `validateCommentQuoteDesync` |
| `ANSIC_QUOTING_OUTSIDE_OBFUSCATION` | `$'\x72\x6d'` outside the obfuscation check | `extractQuotedContent` limitation |
| `FIFTY_SUBCOMMAND_CAP` | Compound command with > 50 segments | `MAX_SUBCOMMANDS_FOR_SECURITY_CHECK` |
| `BARE_SEMICOLON_NODE` | The `node ';' not recognized` warning class — bare `;` separator in contexts the visitor doesn't enumerate | tree-sitter visitor gap |

